# raycast-contacts

A Raycast extension that searches Apple Contacts (macOS native) with a full detail view.

## What it does

- Single command: **Search Contacts** — searches all Apple Contacts via AppleScript
- List view and Detail view (toggleable via dropdown; default is Detail)
- Detail panel shows: phones, emails, addresses, birthday, notes
- Actions: Open in Contacts app, Compose Email, Call, Copy name/email/phone, Refresh

## Architecture

```
src/
  search-contacts.tsx      ← command entry point
  apple-contacts.ts        ← AppleScript fetcher + parser (returns UnifiedContact[])
  hooks.ts                 ← useCachedPromise wrapper (useContacts)
  types.ts                 ← UnifiedContact, ViewMode, ContactField, ContactAddress
  helpers.ts               ← groupByLetter, formatBirthday
  components/
    ContactList.tsx        ← List + Detail UI, ViewModeDropdown
    ContactActions.tsx     ← ActionPanel (open, email, call, copy, refresh)
```

## Key implementation details

- AppleScript uses ASCII 29 (FS), 30 (RS), 28 (VS) as delimiters — never change these
- `run-applescript` package is used (not JXA / child_process)
- Apple Contact labels come through as `_$!<Home>!$_` — `formatType()` in ContactList strips this
- `useCachedPromise` from `@raycast/utils` caches contacts between sessions

## Dev workflow

```bash
npm run dev     # live-reload in Raycast
npm run build   # production build to dist/
npm run lint    # ESLint via @raycast/eslint-config
```

